social_posts.post_text: Part of my 2022 recap. It has been one eventful year and a lot of good things happened in this year and im looking forward to everything good coming in 2023. #2022recap #yearinreview #kendallthemodelscholar #blackwomenphds #blacksocialworkers

Whew, what can I say. They said you wouldn’t live that long and now you’re 30 today. I’m honored to be your wife, you’ve given me a life many people dream about. I’m so glad I met you 15 years ago, and I’ve known you half your life and am proud of how far you’ve come. You’re a man of your word, a fierce protector, and a comedian. God bless you and I love you beyond words. Here’s to getting a front row seat to watching you step into your purpose and I’m looking forward to what’s next. Happy 30th birthday #meetthemorrises #30thbirthday #kendallthemodelscholar

social_posts.post_text: Here is my recap of our 30th birthday trip to the Bahamas 🇧🇸. I know I am late but I have been taking a break from social media while growing this human. We stayed at sandals resort and I highly recommend. It was beautiful and had a private island you could visit by boat. We did a buggy tour all around the city which included going in a cave and visiting jaws beach. We also ate all day and night because I was pregnant and my appetite just came back at that point. I only got sick 🤢 one night and that was the night we had the candlelight dinner on the ocean. Food was too rich. Anyway, we also decided to take pregnancy announcement photos which came out nice. Overall this was an epic trip. Would you rather do a trip or have a party for your milestone birthday? We are doing both 😉 #meetthemorrises #30thbirthday #babyannouncement #kendallthemodelscholar #bahamas #vacationrecap

Check out our most recent visit to our new construction home. It finally looks like a house it’s been a while since I’ve given an update because we had some delays but things are finally moving along now since they finished the framing, we were able to go in and write scriptures all over the walls. Finally getting around to this. This is my doula appreciation post. I want to give a huge shout out to our Doula Sandra. She was a huge blessing to us during our first pregnancy. She provided so much education and support. She constantly checked in on us. She empowered us that way pretty awesome, and she gave us the tools to take care of our son when he was having issues feeding in the beginning (see photos). She gave my two birth support people my husband and mom tools to help me during labor. I highly recommend you get a doula if you have the resources to do so. Too many Black women are dying in childbirth and we need an advocate. I wanted to cry on our last home visit with her. Thank you from the bottom of our hearts @birthherway.doula 💙💙 #blackmotherhood #blackdoula #doulasupport #doulasareessential #boymom #meetthemorrises #kendallthemodelscholar
